":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2021-10-15T17:36:30Z","updated_at":"2022-04-19T18:26:48Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"\r\n1. Admins can directly set access rules for annotators.\r\n2. Create new constructs in system to make some of these rules more clear.\r\n\r\nFor example, as an Annotator\r\nHow many previous tasks can I see? For example if 0 that means I can also see my current task. If 3 I can see up to 3 previous tasks I completed etc.\r\n\r\nWe can think about permissions in backend for this but for some of these more hyper granular controls it may be something we can focus on UI implementation for depending on level of security needed. \r\n\r\nFor some context there are ideas around this already in the Org concept, but we have been moving steadily away from that towards project focused contexts\r\n\r\nIn terms of implementation, using that feature flag approach (not 'modes').","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/diffgram/diffgram/issues/366/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/diffgram/diffgram/issues/366/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}